# .cursorrules
# AIXMOS Project — Cursor AI Rules
# Place this file in the root of the AIXMOS project folder
# Cursor reads this automatically to understand the project

## PROJECT
You are working on AIXMOS — a workforce infrastructure platform.
Read CLAUDE.md for the full project context, service menu, and build queue.

## DESIGN SYSTEM — NEVER CHANGE WITHOUT ASKING
- Primary blue: #1440C4
- Hover blue: #2563EB
- Background: #FFFFFF (white — NO dark mode)
- Surface: #F4F7FF (light blue tint)
- Dark text: #0A1628
- Muted text: rgba(10,22,40,0.50)
- Display font: 'Bebas Neue', sans-serif (Google Fonts)
- Body font: 'DM Sans', sans-serif (Google Fonts)
- Border radius: 8px (inputs), 12px (cards), 16px (sections)
- No gradients. No heavy shadows. No dark backgrounds on main pages.

## STACK
- Pure HTML + CSS + Vanilla JS for landing page and portal
- React (.jsx) for the CHUMMO messaging agent only
- No build step required for HTML files (must work served directly by nginx)
- No TypeScript unless explicitly asked
- No Tailwind (use CSS variables and inline styles)
- No React Router (use vanilla JS view switching in portal)
- External scripts: Google Fonts only (loaded via <link> in <head>)

## FILE STRUCTURE
public/
  index.html        ← Landing page (main AIXMOS site)
  apply.html        ← Intake form page
  thankyou.html     ← Post-submission confirmation
  operator.html     ← Operator application page
portal/
  index.html        ← 4-role private portal
files/
  operator-training.html
  intake-form.html
  pipeline.html
agent/
  ChummoAgent.jsx   ← React Anthropic API messaging agent
docker/
  docker-compose.yml
  nginx-portal.conf
CLAUDE.md           ← Master project context

## GHL PLACEHOLDERS — SEARCH AND REPLACE
YOUR_GHL_97_CHECKOUT_LINK     → $97/month Stripe subscription
YOUR_GHL_LLC_CHECKOUT_LINK    → $397 one-time
YOUR_GHL_3750_CHECKOUT_LINK   → $3,750 down payment
YOUR_GHL_OPERATOR_APPLICATION_LINK → Operator apply form
YOUR_GHL_WEBHOOK_URL          → GHL webhook endpoint

## PRIORITIES (build in this order)
1. thankyou.html — post-payment/form confirmation page
2. operator.html — operator application page
3. Mobile hamburger drawer in index.html
4. Scroll animations in index.html (IntersectionObserver, no libraries)
5. Portal sidebar mobile collapse
6. Server-side auth upgrade (Supabase or JWT)
7. Video player component in portal Training Vault

## RULES
- Never change color system without asking
- Never add npm dependencies without asking
- Never break GHL integration points
- Always test mobile (320px min width)
- HTML files must be self-contained — no external build step
- Keep all files under 1000 lines where possible (split into components if needed)
- Comments in English, concise, explain WHY not WHAT
- Never add inline styles when a CSS variable already covers it
- Preserve existing section IDs (used for anchor links in nav)
- Portal user accounts live in the USERS array in portal/index.html — do not move to external file without asking

## VOICE / COPY RULES
- Friend first. Never corporate.
- "For the people. By the people." is the tagline — never change it
- $10,000/month target appears on every client-facing page
- CHUMMO = caring/listening agent. MOOSE = executing agent. VISION = quality control.
- Operator communications are warm, direct, human — not salesy
